Program: The Forum
Title: Rivers
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p025qhmy
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 8 Sep 2014
The world’s rivers have always played a powerful role in human history. But in today’s world - with air travel, super highways and the internet - do rivers matter less? Bridget Kendall asks Egyptologist Toby Wilkinson, geologist Mathew Wells and actor Olwen Fouéré to probe the watery depths. (Photo: The Huka river in New Zealand. Credit: BBC) Show less